titleStmt.title: A most exact catalogue of the Lords spirituall and temporall, as peers of the realme, in the higher House of Parliament, according to their dignities, offices, and degrees: some other called thither for their assistance, & officers of their attendances And also the names of the knights for the counties, citizens, burgesses for the boroughs, and barons for the ports for the House of Commons, for this Parliament. Whereunto is added a catalogue of the nobility of Ireland: the knights baronets and knights of the bath of England made by King Iames, and King Charles.
Lists. 1628-03-17
titleStmt.author: England and Wales. Parliament.

editionStmt.edition: The fourth edition very much enlarged.
